---
import Legal from '@/layouts/Legal.astro'
---

<Legal
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="How Tiximo collects, uses, and protects your personal data."
  lastUpdated="March 2026"
>
  <section>
    <h2>Who we are</h2>
    <p>Tiximo is an event discovery service accessible via Telegram, WhatsApp, and Discord. References to "Tiximo", "we", "us", or "our" in this policy refer to the Tiximo service. Contact: <a href="mailto:privacy@tiximo.app">privacy@tiximo.app</a></p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>What data we collect</h2>
    <p>When you interact with Tiximo through a messaging platform, we collect:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Your platform user ID (e.g. Telegram ID) and username</li>
      <li>Messages you send to the bot and the responses returned</li>
      <li>Location data you voluntarily share to find nearby events</li>
      <li>Your event interactions — likes, dislikes, bookmarks, and click-throughs</li>
      <li>Approximate city or region derived from location data</li>
    </ul>
    <p>We do not collect your email address, phone number, or payment details. We never have access to any information entered on a third-party ticketing platform.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>How we use your data</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>To find and rank events relevant to your location and preferences</li>
      <li>To personalise future recommendations based on your interaction history</li>
      <li>To maintain your session across conversations</li>
      <li>To improve the overall quality of the service</li>
    </ul>
    <p>We do not sell your data. We do not use your data for advertising.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Legal basis (UK GDPR)</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Legitimate interests</strong> — personalising event recommendations based on your usage of the service</li>
      <li><strong>Consent</strong> — location data, which you share voluntarily by sending it to the bot</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Data storage</h2>
    <p>Your data is stored in a PostgreSQL database hosted on Neon (EU region). Interaction signals are stored in ClickHouse Cloud. Both providers operate under appropriate data processing agreements.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Data retention</h2>
    <p>We retain your data for as long as you use the service. You can request deletion at any time — see Your rights below.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Third parties</h2>
    <p>When you click through to a ticketing platform (Ticketmaster, Eventbrite, DICE, etc.), you are subject to their privacy policies. We share no personal data with these platforms. We may earn a referral commission on purchases — this does not affect your price or data.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Your rights</h2>
    <p>Under UK GDPR you have the right to access, correct, or delete your data. You can:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Send <strong>/mydata</strong> to the bot to see what we hold</li>
      <li>Send <strong>/deleteaccount</strong> to permanently delete all your data</li>
      <li>Email <a href="mailto:privacy@tiximo.app">privacy@tiximo.app</a> for any other requests</li>
    </ul>
    <p>We will respond to requests within 30 days. You also have the right to lodge a complaint with the <a href="https://ico.org.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ICO</a>.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Cookies</h2>
    <p>This website uses a minimal session cookie. See our <a href="/cookies">Cookie Policy</a> for details.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
    <p>We may update this policy from time to time. The date at the top of the page reflects the most recent revision. Continued use of the service after changes constitutes acceptance.</p>
  </section>
</Legal>
